{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I don't speak English."},{"time":2000,"text":"I start speaking English, learning English, about a year ago."},{"time":6000,"text":"I speak French and I grew up with French, so my English is Franglais."},{"time":13000,"text":"I'm born in the Western Congo, in an area around here,"},{"time":18000,"text":"and then went to university in Kisangani."},{"time":23000,"text":"And after I finished, I went to this area, the Ituri Forest."},{"time":27000,"text":"But what I've been doing --"},{"time":29000,"text":"when I was about 14, I grew in my uncle's house."},{"time":36000,"text":"And my father was a soldier,"},{"time":39000,"text":"and my uncle was a fisherman and also a poacher."},{"time":43000,"text":"What I've been doing from 14 to 17 was,"},{"time":48000,"text":"I was assisting them collecting ivory tusk, meat"},{"time":55000,"text":"and whatever they were killing, poaching, hunting in the forest,"},{"time":59000,"text":"bring it in the main city to get access to the market."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64000,"text":"But finally, I got myself involved."},{"time":68000,"text":"Around 17 to 20 years, I became, myself, a poacher."},{"time":75000,"text":"And I wanted to do it, because -- I believed -- to continue my studies."},{"time":80000,"text":"I wanted to go to university, but my father was poor, my uncle even."},{"time":84000,"text":"So, I did it."},{"time":86000,"text":"And for three to four years, I went to university."},{"time":90000,"text":"For three times, I applied to biomedical science, to be a doctor."},{"time":96000,"text":"I didn't succeed."},{"time":98000,"text":"I was having my inscriptions, my admission to biology."},{"time":103000,"text":"And I said, \"No way, I'm not doing it."},{"time":105000,"text":"My family's poor, my area don't have better health care."},{"time":109000,"text":"I want to be a doctor to serve them.\""},{"time":111000,"text":"Three times, that means three years, and I start getting old."},{"time":116000,"text":"I say, \"Oh, no, I continue.\""},{"time":118000,"text":"So, I did tropical ecology and plant botany."},{"time":124000,"text":"When I finished, I went to the Ituri Forest for my internship."},{"time":128000,"text":"It's where I really getting passion with what I'm doing"},{"time":132000,"text":"right up to now -- I'm standing in front of you --"},{"time":136000,"text":"doing botany and wildlife conservation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":140000,"text":"That time the Ituri Forest was created as a forest reserve"},{"time":144000,"text":"with some animals and also plants."},{"time":149000,"text":"And the training center there was built"},{"time":151000,"text":"around the scientific Congolese staff"},{"time":156000,"text":"and some American scientists also."},{"time":159000,"text":"So, the Okapi Faunal Reserve protects number --"},{"time":162000,"text":"I think that is the largest number of elephants"},{"time":166000,"text":"we have right now in protected areas in Congo."},{"time":169000,"text":"It has also chimpanzees."},{"time":171000,"text":"And it has been named Okapi Faunal Reserve"},{"time":174000,"text":"because of this beautiful creature."},{"time":177000,"text":"That is a forest giraffe."},{"time":179000,"text":"I think you guys know it quite well."},{"time":182000,"text":"Here we have savanna giraffes,"},{"time":184000,"text":"but through evolution we have this forest giraffe"},{"time":189000,"text":"that lives only in Congo."},{"time":191000,"text":"It has also some beautiful primates."},{"time":194000,"text":"Thirteen species -- highest diversity we can find in one single area in Africa."},{"time":201000,"text":"And it has the Ituri Forest itself --"},{"time":204000,"text":"about 1,300 species of plants, so far known."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209000,"text":"I joined the Wildlife Conservation Society, working there, in 1995,"},{"time":215000,"text":"but I started working with them as a student in 1991."},{"time":218000,"text":"I was appointed as a teaching assistant at my university"},{"time":223000,"text":"because I accomplished with honor."},{"time":227000,"text":"But I didn't like the way -- the instruction I got was very poor."},{"time":232000,"text":"And I wanted to be formed to a training center and a research center."},{"time":236000,"text":"With the end of the dictatorship regime of Mobutu Sese Seko,"},{"time":241000,"text":"that most of you know, life became very, very difficult."},{"time":246000,"text":"And the work we have been doing"},{"time":248000,"text":"was completely difficult to do and to achieve it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252000,"text":"When Kabila started his movement to liberate Congo,"},{"time":258000,"text":"so Mobutu soldiers started moving and retreated."},{"time":262000,"text":"So they started fleeing from the east to the west."},{"time":266000,"text":"And the Okapi Faunal Reserve is there,"},{"time":269000,"text":"so there was a road from Goma, somewhere here,"},{"time":274000,"text":"and coming like this."},{"time":276000,"text":"So they might go through, pass through the Okapi Faunal Reserve."},{"time":281000,"text":"Congo has five of the world's richest sites of protected area,"},{"time":287000,"text":"and the Okapi Faunal Reserve is one of them."},{"time":290000,"text":"So soldier was fleeing in the Okapi Faunal Reserve."},{"time":293000,"text":"On their way, they looted everything."},{"time":297000,"text":"Torture, wars -- oh, my God, you can't believe."},{"time":300000,"text":"Every person was looking his way -- where to go, we don't know."},{"time":305000,"text":"And it was for us, the young, the first time really"},{"time":308000,"text":"we hear the language of war, of guns."},{"time":313000,"text":"And even people who faced the rebellion of 1963,"},{"time":318000,"text":"after our independence, they didn't believe what was happening."},{"time":324000,"text":"They were killing people. They were doing whatever they want"},{"time":326000,"text":"because they have power."},{"time":328000,"text":"Who have been doing that?"},{"time":330000,"text":"Young children. Child soldiers."},{"time":333000,"text":"You can't ask him how old he is because he has guns."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338000,"text":"But I was from the west, working in the east."},{"time":341000,"text":"I even [at] that time was not speaking Swahili."},{"time":345000,"text":"And when they came, they looted everything."},{"time":347000,"text":"You can't speak Lingala because Lingala was from Mobutu,"},{"time":351000,"text":"and everyone speaking Lingala is soldier."},{"time":354000,"text":"And I was from the same area to him."},{"time":356000,"text":"All my friends said, we are leaving because we are a target."},{"time":359000,"text":"But I'm not going to the east, because I don't know Swahili."},{"time":363000,"text":"I stay. If I go, I will be killed."},{"time":365000,"text":"I can't go back to my area -- it's more than 1,000 kilometers [away]."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369000,"text":"I stayed after they looted everything."},{"time":372000,"text":"We have been doing research on botany,"},{"time":375000,"text":"and we have a small herbarium of 4,500 sheets of plants."},{"time":381000,"text":"We cut, we dry and we packed them,"},{"time":383000,"text":"we mounted them on a folder."},{"time":386000,"text":"Purpose: so that we start them for agriculture,"},{"time":390000,"text":"for medicine, for whatever, and for science,"},{"time":393000,"text":"for the study of the flora and the change of the forest."},{"time":397000,"text":"That is people moving around, that's even Pygmies."},{"time":400000,"text":"And this is a bright guy, hard-working person, and Pygmy."},{"time":407000,"text":"I've been working with him about 10 years."},{"time":410000,"text":"And with soldiers, they went to the forest for poaching elephants."},{"time":415000,"text":"Because he's Pygmy, he knows how to track elephants in the forest."},{"time":419000,"text":"He has been attacked by a leopard and they abandon him in the forest."},{"time":425000,"text":"They came to told me, I have to save him."},{"time":428000,"text":"And what I did, I gave him just antibiotics"},{"time":431000,"text":"that we care for tuberculosis."},{"time":435000,"text":"And fortunately, I saved his life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":438000,"text":"And that was the language of the war."},{"time":442000,"text":"Everywhere there has been constant extraction of mineral,"},{"time":447000,"text":"killing animals, the logging timbers and so on."},{"time":451000,"text":"And what of important things --"},{"time":453000,"text":"I think all of you here have a cell phone."},{"time":456000,"text":"That mineral has killed a lot:"},{"time":458000,"text":"five millions of Congolese have gone because of this"},{"time":462000,"text":"Colombo-Tantalite -- they call it Coltan --"},{"time":465000,"text":"that they use it to make cell phones"},{"time":468000,"text":"and it has been in that area, all over in Congo. Extraction,"},{"time":473000,"text":"and good, big business of the war."}]},{"cues":[{"time":476000,"text":"And what I did for the first war, after we have lost everything,"},{"time":482000,"text":"I have to save something, even myself, my life and life of the staff."},{"time":486000,"text":"I buried some of our new vehicle engines, I buried it to save it."},{"time":492000,"text":"And some of equipment went with them,"},{"time":494000,"text":"on the top of the canopy, to save it."},{"time":496000,"text":"He's not collecting plants, he's going to save our equipment"},{"time":499000,"text":"on the canopy."},{"time":501000,"text":"And with the material that's left --"},{"time":503000,"text":"because they wanted to destroy it, to burn it,"},{"time":506000,"text":"they didn't understand it, they didn't go to school --"},{"time":508000,"text":"I packed it."},{"time":510000,"text":"And that is me, going to, hurrying to Uganda,"},{"time":514000,"text":"to try to save that 4,000 material,"},{"time":517000,"text":"with people carrying them on the bikes, bicycles."},{"time":522000,"text":"And after that, we succeeded."},{"time":524000,"text":"I housed that 4,000 material at the herbarium of Makerere University."},{"time":529000,"text":"And after the war, I have been able to bring it back home,"},{"time":533000,"text":"so that we continue our studies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":535000,"text":"The second war came while we didn't expect it."},{"time":539000,"text":"With friends, we had been sitting and watching match football,"},{"time":543000,"text":"and having some good music with WorldSpace radio,"},{"time":547000,"text":"when it started, I think."},{"time":549000,"text":"So, it was so bad."},{"time":552000,"text":"We heard that now from the east again the war started,"},{"time":555000,"text":"and it's going fast."},{"time":557000,"text":"This time I think Kabila will go in place of, as he did with Mobutu."},{"time":562000,"text":"And the reserve was a target to the rebels."},{"time":566000,"text":"Three different movements and two militia acting in the same area"},{"time":572000,"text":"and competing for natural resources."},{"time":575000,"text":"And there was no way to work."},{"time":577000,"text":"They destroy everything."},{"time":579000,"text":"Poaching -- oh, no way."},{"time":581000,"text":"And that's the powerful men. We have to meet and to talk to them."},{"time":587000,"text":"What's the regulation of the reserve"},{"time":589000,"text":"and what is the regulation of the parks?"},{"time":591000,"text":"And they can't do what they are doing."},{"time":594000,"text":"So we went to meet them."},{"time":596000,"text":"That is Coltan extraction, gold mining."}]},{"cues":[{"time":600000,"text":"So, we started talking with them,"},{"time":602000,"text":"convincing them that we are in a protected area."},{"time":604000,"text":"There are regulations"},{"time":606000,"text":"that it's prohibited to do logging, mining and poaching, specifically."},{"time":612000,"text":"But they said, \"You guys,"},{"time":614000,"text":"you think that soldiers who are dying are not important,"},{"time":618000,"text":"and your animals you are protecting are most important."},{"time":623000,"text":"We don't think so."},{"time":625000,"text":"We have to do it, because to let our movement advance.\""},{"time":629000,"text":"I say, \"No way, you are not going to do it here.\""},{"time":632000,"text":"We started talking with them and I was negotiating."},{"time":635000,"text":"Tried to protect our equipment, tried to protect our staff"},{"time":640000,"text":"and the villages of about 1,500 people."},{"time":644000,"text":"And we continued."}]},{"cues":[{"time":646000,"text":"But I was doing that, negotiating with them."},{"time":649000,"text":"Sometimes we are having meeting"},{"time":651000,"text":"and they are talking with Jean-Pierre Bemba,"},{"time":653000,"text":"with Mbusa Nyamwisi, with Kabila, and I'm there."},{"time":657000,"text":"Sometimes, they talk to my own language, that is, Lingala."},{"time":660000,"text":"I hear it and what strategy they are doing, what they are planning."},{"time":664000,"text":"Sometimes, they are having a helicopter"},{"time":666000,"text":"to supply them with ammunition and so on."},{"time":668000,"text":"They used me to carry that, and I was doing counting,"},{"time":673000,"text":"what comes from where, and where, and where."},{"time":675000,"text":"I had only this equipment -- my satellite phone, my computer"},{"time":681000,"text":"and a plastic solar panel -- that I hide it in the forest."},{"time":687000,"text":"And every time, daily, after we have meeting,"},{"time":691000,"text":"what compromise we have, whatever,"},{"time":695000,"text":"I go, I write a short email, send it."},{"time":698000,"text":"I don't know how many people I had on my address."},{"time":702000,"text":"I sent the message: what is going about the progress of the war"},{"time":706000,"text":"and what they are planning to do."},{"time":708000,"text":"They started suspecting that what we do on the morning,"},{"time":712000,"text":"and the afternoon, it's on the news, BBC, RFI."},{"time":715000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":716000,"text":"Something might be going on."},{"time":718000,"text":"And one day, we went for a meeting."},{"time":720000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":722000,"text":"Sorry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726000,"text":"One day, we went to meet the Chief Commander."},{"time":728000,"text":"He had the same iridium cell phone like me."},{"time":731000,"text":"And he asked me, \"Do you know how to use this?\""},{"time":733000,"text":"I said, \"I have never seen it."},{"time":735000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":736000,"text":"I don't know.\""},{"time":738000,"text":"And I had mine on my pocket."},{"time":740000,"text":"So, it was a chance that they trusted me a lot."},{"time":742000,"text":"They didn't -- they was not looking on me."},{"time":744000,"text":"So I was scared."},{"time":746000,"text":"And when we finished the meeting, I went to return it in the forest."},{"time":750000,"text":"And I was sending news, doing whatever,"},{"time":754000,"text":"reporting daily to the U.N., to UNESCO, to our institution in New York,"},{"time":759000,"text":"what have been going."},{"time":761000,"text":"And for that, they have been having big pressure to leave, to free the area."},{"time":766000,"text":"Because there was no way --"},{"time":768000,"text":"whatever they do, it's known the same time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":770000,"text":"During the first two rebellions, they killed all animals in the zoo."},{"time":775000,"text":"We have a zoo of 14 Okapis, and one of them was pregnant."},{"time":779000,"text":"And during the war, after a week of heavy war, fighting in the area,"},{"time":785000,"text":"we succeeded: we had the first Okapi."},{"time":787000,"text":"This is the only trouser and shirt remind me of this."},{"time":790000,"text":"This is not local population, this is rebels."},{"time":793000,"text":"They are now happy sending the news"},{"time":795000,"text":"that they have protected the Okapi with the war,"},{"time":797000,"text":"because we sent the news that they are killing"},{"time":800000,"text":"and poaching everywhere."},{"time":801000,"text":"After a week, we celebrated the birthday of that Okapi,"},{"time":806000,"text":"they killed an elephant, just 50 meters to the area"},{"time":810000,"text":"where the zoo, where Okapi was born."},{"time":813000,"text":"And I was mad."},{"time":814000,"text":"I oppose it -- that they are now going to dissect it,"},{"time":816000,"text":"until I do my report and then I see the Chief Commander."},{"time":822000,"text":"And I succeeded."},{"time":824000,"text":"The elephant just decayed and they just got the tusks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":829000,"text":"What we are doing after that -- that was the situation of the war --"},{"time":834000,"text":"we have to rebuild."},{"time":836000,"text":"I had some money. I was paid 150 dollars."},{"time":839000,"text":"I devoted half of it to rebuild the herbarium,"},{"time":845000,"text":"because we didn't have good infrastructure to start plants."},{"time":848000,"text":"Wildlife Conservation Society more dealing with plants."},{"time":852000,"text":"I started this with 70 dollars,"},{"time":855000,"text":"and start fundraising money to where I've been going."},{"time":859000,"text":"I had opportunity to go all over,"},{"time":861000,"text":"where herbarium for my African material is."},{"time":864000,"text":"And they supported me a bit, and I built this."},{"time":869000,"text":"Now, it's doing work to train young Congolese."}]},{"cues":[{"time":874000,"text":"And also, what one of the speciality we are doing,"},{"time":877000,"text":"my design is tracking the global warming effect on biodiversity,"},{"time":883000,"text":"and what the impacts of the Ituri Forest is playing to uptake carbon."},{"time":888000,"text":"This is one of the studies we are doing on a 40-hectare plot,"},{"time":892000,"text":"where we have tagged trees and lianas from one centimeters,"},{"time":896000,"text":"and we are tracking them."},{"time":898000,"text":"We have now data of about 15 years,"},{"time":902000,"text":"to see how that forest is contributing to the carbon reductions."},{"time":909000,"text":"And that is -- I think it's difficult for me."},{"time":914000,"text":"This is a very embarrassing talk, I know."},{"time":917000,"text":"I don't know where to start, where to finish it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":920000,"text":"When I was thinking to come here,"},{"time":922000,"text":"what best title I wanted to say to my talk, I didn't find this."},{"time":927000,"text":"But now I think that I would have titled it, \"The Language of Guns.\""},{"time":932000,"text":"Where are you people?"},{"time":934000,"text":"Now we are talking about reconstitution, rebuild Africa."},{"time":939000,"text":"But is gun industries a tool to rebuild, or is it a game?"},{"time":947000,"text":"I think we see the war like a game --"},{"time":952000,"text":"like soccer, football."},{"time":954000,"text":"Everybody is happy, but see what it's doing,"},{"time":959000,"text":"see what is going in Darfur."},{"time":961000,"text":"Now we say, oh, my God."},{"time":962000,"text":"See what the wars in Rwanda."},{"time":964000,"text":"That's because of the language of guns."},{"time":968000,"text":"I don't think that someone may blame Google,"},{"time":972000,"text":"because it's doing the right things,"},{"time":975000,"text":"even if people like Al-Qaeda are using Google"},{"time":978000,"text":"to connect between them."},{"time":980000,"text":"But it's serving millions for the best."},{"time":983000,"text":"But what is doing with gun industries?"},{"time":986000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":988000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":993000,"text":"Chris Anderson: Thank you, thank you."},{"time":995000,"text":"Just wait over there."},{"time":998000,"text":"It's an amazing story."},{"time":1000000,"text":"I suspect a lot of people here have the same question I have."},{"time":1005000,"text":"How can we help you?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1010000,"text":"Corneille Ewango: That's really embarrassing questions."},{"time":1014000,"text":"I think that now I feel nervous."},{"time":1016000,"text":"And I think, helping us, people are acting sometimes by ignorance."},{"time":1022000,"text":"I did it myself."},{"time":1024000,"text":"If I know when I was young,"},{"time":1026000,"text":"that [by] killing an elephant, I'm destroying biodiversity,"},{"time":1029000,"text":"I would not have done it."},{"time":1031000,"text":"Many, many of you have seen the talents of Africans,"},{"time":1035000,"text":"but there are few who are going to school."},{"time":1039000,"text":"Many are dying because of all those kind of pandemics,"},{"time":1044000,"text":"HIV, malaria, poverty, not going to school."},{"time":1049000,"text":"What you can assist us, it's by building capacities."},{"time":1053000,"text":"How many have got opportunity like me"},{"time":1055000,"text":"to go to U.S., do a master's?"},{"time":1057000,"text":"And go -- now, I'm in the Netherlands to do a Ph.D."},{"time":1060000,"text":"But many of them are just here, because they don't have money."},{"time":1063000,"text":"And they can't go even to university."},{"time":1066000,"text":"They can't even attain the bachelor's degree."},{"time":1069000,"text":"Building capacities for the young generation"},{"time":1073000,"text":"is going to make a better generation"},{"time":1075000,"text":"and a better future tomorrow for Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1078000,"text":"CA: Thank you, thank you."},{"time":1079000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}